title: Appointments of Private Columbaria Appeal Board members
content_text: A spokesman for the Food and Health Bureau said that the regulation of private columbaria involves complicated and sensitive issues, requiring contributions from a balanced mix of panel members from diverse backgrounds, including expertise in legal, planning, land, building, transport, environment and commercial business fields.  "Appointment to the second term ensures that the Appeal Board will continue to have a good mix of members from various professional fields with profound experience and expertise that is relevant to the work of the Board. We are indebted to all members for their contributions in the first term and we are confident that members of the second term will keep rising to the challenges and tender valued

term and we are confident that members of the second term will keep rising to the challenges and tender valued advice to the Board in reviewing appeal cases from all perspectives," said the spokesman. The Government also paid tribute to outgoing members, Mrs Pamela Chan Wong Shui, Mr Ivan Fu Chin-shing and Miss Vivian Yu Yuk-ying, for their contributions and support over the past years. The Private Columbaria Appeal Board is a statutory body established under section 83 of the Private Columbaria Ordinance (Cap. 630) to hear and determine an appeal lodged by an applicant or a holder of a specified instrument who is aggrieved

hear and determine an appeal lodged by an applicant or a holder of a specified instrument who is aggrieved by a decision made by the Private Columbaria Licensing Board or the Director of Food and Environmental Hygiene referred to in section 84(1) of the Ordinance. The membership list of the Appeal Board for the second term is as follows: Chairperson Mr Ambrose Ho, SC Deputy Chairpersons Mr Frederick Chan Hing-fai Mr Kenneth Kwok Hing-wai, SC Dr William Wong Ming-fung, SC Members Ms Bonnie Chan Jo-ying Dr Chau Chi-kwan Mr Chiu Kam-kuen Dr Catherine
